Case called at 10:08 am [Clerk SH]
[Reserve Judge Sarah O'Brien presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Rebecca M Frye in court with Attorney Joseph Francis Fischer. DA Susan V. Happ appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
DA Happ informs the Court that they will be filing amended complaint, with 3 counts of misdemeanor theft, need a bit more time
Atty Fischer reviews plea agreement; DA Happ submits amended complaint
Sentencing arguments by Counsel; Statements by Ms. Frye; Statement by Gina Skrowback

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered on Counts #1, #2, & #3; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.

On Counts #1, #2 & #3, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 2 years, each count, concurrent, with conditions:
--To pay restitution of $2508.32 payable to Wal-Mart
--To pay 10% restitution processing fee
--To undergo any assessment, treatment or counseling as required per Agent
--To pay costs of $729 ($243 each count)
--To pay $200 DNA Surcharge on Count #1 
Court waives DNA Surcharge on Counts #2 & #3, presents basis including finding that restitution would not be able to be paid during probation if additional fees are imposed due to indigency.

Days credit for time already served: 0 days
Recess: 10:31 am
Status conference on August 29, 2014 at 10:00 am.
Pre-trial conference on August 6, 2014 at 01:40 pm.
